Cork: Robert Hooke

"I no sooner discerned

these (which were indeed

the first microscopical

pores I have ever saw ... )

but me thought I had with

the discovery of them,

perfectly hinted to me the

true and intelligible reason

for all the phenomena of

cork"

Micrographia (1665)

Hooke: first to use the term "cell", from Latin "cella" a small compartment 2
